<HEADLINE>
Turkey allocates 2.5 million dollars for Katrina victims
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
ANKARA, Sept 13
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Turkey has allocated 2.5 million dollars 
to contribute to relief efforts after Hurricane Katrina devastated 
the US Gulf Coast, the foreign ministry announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said 1.5 million dollars was sent to the US Red 
Cross and the remaining funds would be spent on humanitarian 
supplies to be dispatched to the United States in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
Washington said Monday that 118 countries have provided aid to 
victims of Hurricane Katrina, which claimed at least 513 lives.
</P>
